  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "A pleasant crag that is well worth a morning or afternoon visit. Greggered is a small village; the nearest grocery shop is probably in Lindome.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:greggered"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A pleasant crag that is well worth a morning or afternoon. Greggered is a small village; the nearest grocery shop is probably in Lindome.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kollektivtrafik": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Public transport",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The nearest known bus stop is Greggereds Kapell, served by bus 763. The journey from Mölndal C takes 30–70 minutes.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "From Gothenburg, take exit 63 at Kållered, go straight on at the first roundabout, turn left, cross the motorway and continue straight ahead eastwards. After a couple of kilometres, turn left at the sign for Greggered.\n\nAlternatively, take exit 62 (Lindome S) and head towards Hällesåker. After a while, turn left at the sign for Greggered.\n\nIn Greggered, which is a small village, park in the small gravel area. Bear in mind that the farmer who owns it needs to be able to park his lorry there.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          }
        },
        "miljo": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Environment",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Deciduous woodland, with a fine view from the ledge. Not particularly accessible with a pushchair. To reach the top of the crag, walk to the right-hand end of the ledge. The “woodland” around Greggered is quite small. Pack out your shit!",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          }
        },
        "accessinformation": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access information",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Make sure you park so that the landowner has room for his lorry. Do not damage the fence! Sound carries between the crag and the nearest neighbours, so it would be unwise to disturb them (i.e. keep the noise down).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          }
        },
        "huvudklippan": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Main crag",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "All routes on the “main crag” are bolted. From Rastafari to Obladi Obladi, this section is 20 metres high.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hyllan": {
          "title": {
            "text": "The ledge",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Before the metal ladder, there are these two routes:",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:greggered"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
